# GOI GIS Tool — Known State (Manual)

Use this rule only when a task risks regressions or needs full context alignment.

## Canonical & constraints
- Canonical file: `coordinate_converter Claude.html` (single-file app).
- Offline-first, OPSEC-aware. No silent network calls. No frameworks/build step.

## “Do not break these” invariants
- No silent geolocation at startup (permission UX + OPSEC).
- Geolocation works only in secure context; UI must reflect this.
- Geolocation is single-shot only (`getCurrentPosition`); continuous `watchPosition` tracking has been removed in the pre-GIS cleanup — do not reintroduce it casually.
- When offline, prefer IndexedDB cached tiles + placeholders; do not add auto-online fallbacks.
- Named areas may be legacy (missing `z0/z1`) and must keep working.
- OPSEC strict mode (`state.opsecStrict`) must block external geocoding fetches.
- i18n:
  - `data-i18n` → `textContent` default
  - `data-i18n-html` → `innerHTML` only for explicit rich-text help strings
- Persisted storage must be sanitized/clamped on load (localStorage can be corrupted).
- Event handlers for tool modes should be idempotent + cleaned up on cancel/Esc.
- GIS Phase 1 stores are intentionally hybrid/additive:
  - `state.mapWaypoints[]` remains the waypoint source of truth.
  - `state.gisTracks[]` cap 50 and `state.gisPolygons[]` cap 50 store new GeoJSON-native line/polygon features.
  - `state.gisLayers[]` cap 20 always includes seed layers `lay-seed-waypoints`, `lay-seed-tracks`, `lay-seed-polygons`.
  - `state.gisSelection`, `state.undoStack`, and `state.redoStack` are transient; do not persist or expose global undo UI until the dedicated undo phase.
  - Use `gisAllAsFeatureCollection()` for unified reads; do not migrate `mapWaypoints[]` into a unified store before the planned Phase 6 decision.

## Known pitfalls to avoid
- Avoid expanding `innerHTML` surfaces beyond the intended i18n help blocks.

## GIS-first layout (current default, net replacement of classic home)
- Boot layout is **GIS viewer/planner** (`body.gis-mode`), with:
  - Compact top `<header>` (global controls) + `<nav id="appTopbar">` (tabs + Converti CTA + Altri strumenti).
  - Full-screen map inside `#gisMapMount` (the `#miniMap` is reparented there at init by `gisInit()`).
  - Classic home cards (paste / manual input / geocoding / results / tools strip) are **hidden when in their home slots** (`body.gis-mode > main > …` selectors) and appear only when reparented into the tab drawer / convert modal / tools modal.
- Do not clone sections — always move them with `appendChild` and restore them via the `GIS_HOME_SLOTS` map. Cloning breaks already-cabled event listeners.
- Tabs reparent into `<aside id="tabDrawer">`; secondary tools reparent into `<dialog id="toolsModal">`'s panel slot; conversion flow reparents into `<dialog id="convertModal">`.
- `state.activeTab` values are whitelisted by `GIS_VALID_TABS`; any unknown value must be coerced to `null` on load.
- `mapSize` is forced to `"full"` when entering GIS mode; the legacy `mm-full` fixed-float for `#offlineTilePanel` is neutralized via `.tab-drawer-body #offlineTilePanel` / `.tools-panel-wrap #offlineTilePanel` overrides.
- The on-map coverage button (`[data-role="offline-panel-open"]`) is intercepted in capture phase to open the `layers` tab — never call `state.offlineDownloadVisible = true` on its own in GIS mode and expect to see the panel.
- `gisInit()` is idempotent (guarded by `_gisInitDone`). It runs at the end of `init()`, after `applyLanguage` and before `initMiniMapOnStartup` so the first map render happens inside `#gisMapMount`.

## Waypoints modal (split from sec-track)
- `state.mapWaypoints` is the single source of truth for map waypoints; the modal never duplicates the array. Rendering in the modal's `#wp-list` must be kept in sync with `renderMapWaypointsList()` (both are called by `renderMapWaypointsAll()`).
- The Waypoints tab is a `tab-as-modal`: `GIS_TAB_SECTIONS.waypoints === "sec-waypoints"` and `"waypoints"` is in `GIS_TABS_AS_MODAL`. Opening reparents `sec-waypoints` into the dialog body via `gisMoveSectionTo`, closing calls `gisRestoreSection("sec-waypoints")`. Do not clone; do not render the section twice.
- `state.waypointsModalOpen` and `state.waypointEditorDraft` are transient. The modal persists only through the canonical `mapWaypoints[]`; the separate Phase 1 GIS stores are not a waypoint-modal duplicate.
- Import/export of waypoints uses only GeoJSON (not a new format). Import goes through `spatialGeojsonTextToFeatureCollection` → `spatialNormalizeGeoJSON` → filter `Point`; export reuses `spatialBuildFeatureCollectionFromAppState` filtered to `properties.kind === "waypoint"`. The cap of 200 waypoints must be respected (same as `saveStore`).
- Sanitize on load already clamps `mapWaypoints` to 200 and `name` to 60 chars. The modal also clamps `meta.notes` to 500 chars (same ceiling used by `favorites.notes`).
